hello I'm Mosen a cloud support engineer
here at AWS office in Sydney today I'm
going to show you how to increase the
custom origin response timeout in Amazon
cloudfront let's get
started after logging into AWS
Management console navigate to Amazon
cloudfront
console choose your Cloud front
distribution in the distribution Pane
and then select the ID of distribution
that you want to edit navigate to origin
tab to open the list of origin pages in
the list of origin select the checkbox
next to the origin name that you want to
edit then choose edit on the settings
page navigate to additional settings and
then click onto the drop- down
menu in the response timeout section
enter the new timeout value that you
want to
edit the default respon respon timeout
value is 30 seconds and the value here
can go up to 60 seconds to configure a
response timeout value greater than 60
seconds you must request a quota
increase choose save
changes so now you know how to increase
the custom origin response timeout in
Amazon
cloudfront thanks for watching and happy
cloud computing from all of us here at
AWS goodbye
